      <relatedmaterial id="aspace_26a99721e341cf835699a70f7ebf1602">
         <head>Associated Materials</head>
         <p>Palestine Statehood Committee: "Concerning the campaigns for a Jewish Army; to save the Jewish people of Europe and the establishment of a Hebrew Republic in Palestine" Papers, MS 690. Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </relatedmaterial>
      <bioghist id="aspace_0286e851ff5af9a0a8566069f71f7d06">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Institute for Mediterranean Affairs was chartered by the University of the State of New York. It focused on developing an understanding of the historical and contemporary political and socio-economic problems of regions that border the Mediterranean Sea, especially the Middle East and North Africa.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_040271d2cfb16b8123201aa54ff53e09">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of subject files, correspondence, administrative files, and publications documenting the activities of the Institute for Mediterranean Affairs.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
